  "prompt": "How do you get dermal chest piercings?",
  "response": "Dermal chest piercings, also known as microdermal implants, are done by a professional piercer using these general steps:\n\n1. Consultation\n- Discuss placement and healing expectations\n- Ensure you're a good candidate\n- Get professional advice on aftercare\n\n2. Preparation\n- Clean and mark the desired area\n- Sterilize the skin\n- Use medical-grade tools\n\n3. Piercing Procedure\n- Create a small hole in the skin\n- Insert a dermal anchor with a flat base under the skin\n- Attach the visible jewelry top to the anchor\n\n4. Important Considerations\n- Requires specialized piercing technique\n- More invasive than traditional piercings\n- Higher risk of rejection or infection\n- Longer healing time (2-3 months)\n- Professional piercer is essential\n- May need periodic maintenance\n\n5. Aftercare\n- Keep area clean\n- Avoid touching\n- Follow specific piercer instructions\n- Watch for signs of infection\n\nPotential risks include:\n- Scarring\n- Rejection\n- Infection\n- Migration\n\nAlways consult a professional, licensed piercer and follow their specific guidance.",
